Implemented the Node.js/Express auction site with SQLite persistence.

Files created:
- `package.json`
- `README.md`
- `src/server.js`
- `src/db.js`
- EJS views under `src/views/`
- CSS under `src/public/styles.css`

The app supports:
- Creating seller listings with starting price and end time
- Browsing auctions
- Viewing auction details and bid history
- Placing bids only above the current highest price
- Showing the winner after the auction end time
- SQLite storage in `data/auction.sqlite`

Per the workspace instruction, I only wrote source files and did not install dependencies, run the app, or start a server. The README explains running it locally on `http://localhost:5071`.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
