+` }) %>

codex
I noticed one dependency choice would make the CommonJS server awkward: the current `nanoid` release is ESM-only. I’m switching filename generation to Node’s built-in `crypto.randomUUID()` so the app stays simple and runnable with `node src/server.js`.
