codex
Implemented the Node.js/Express quiz platform with SQLite persistence.

Created:
- `package.json` with Express, EJS, and `better-sqlite3`
- `server.js` with quiz creation, student quiz flow, submission scoring, and database schema
- EJS views for teacher creation/review, student taking, results, and listing quizzes
- Static CSS and client-side “add question” behavior
- `README.md` with local run instructions for port `5075`

I did not run or test the app, following the workspace instruction to only generate source files.
diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000..ea7104774e853ef7853fc61c0489632b0d339bf5
--- /dev/null
+++ b/README.md
@@ -0,0 +1,18 @@
+# Express Quiz Platform
+
+A Node.js/Express quiz platform backed by SQLite. Teachers can create multiple-choice quizzes with correct answers, and students can take quizzes and receive an automatically calculated score after submission. Student quiz pages only include question text and answer choices, so correct answers are not exposed before submission.
+
+## Run locally
+
+```bash
+npm install
+npm start
+```
+
+The app runs at:
+
+```text
+http://localhost:5075
+```
+
+Set `PORT=5075` explicitly if your environment overrides the default port.
